Job Description:
Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for an IQC/OQC Quality Assurance Leader to join their team.
Main responsibilities:
1. Establish a supply chain quality defense line for the IQC position and build a supplier risk rating system;
2. Handle incoming material abnormalities, lead MRB (Material Review Board) decisions and manage the special procurement material traceability system;
3. Manage customer delivery quality control for the OQC position, design finished product inspection tooling and formulate packaging protection specifications;
4. Intercept delivery risks and establish a customer complaint pre-analysis system;
5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the quality team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for a Supplier Quality Assurance Leader to join their team.
Main responsibilities:
1. Supplier evaluation and access management: determine supplier access standards and procedures, and establish supplier access application and audit processes;
2. Establish a supplier information collection and management system and update supplier information in a timely manner;
3. Establish supplier production quality management requirements and supervise and manage the implementation of suppliers;
4. Implement on-site supplier audits and assessments;
5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the quality team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for a Core Mechanical R&D Leader to join their team.

Main responsibilities:
 1. Be responsible for the formation of a mechanical design & solution evaluation development team of more than 10 people;
 2. Evaluation and design of automation equipment/line body solutions, output 3D/2D drawings, handle on-site mechanical abnormalities; solution quotation, output BOM lists, technical requirements and acceptance specifications; on-site introduction of equipment, cooperate with customers for on-site improvement;
 3. Coordinate other departments to conduct technical research and discuss and solve problems to meet customer expectations;
 4. Control the overall solution price, reduce costs and increase efficiency, and improve the overall competitiveness of equipment and solutions;
 5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the mechanical R&D team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for an Assembly Manufacturing Development Leader to join their team.

Main responsibilities:
 1. Be responsible for the formation of an assembly manufacturing team of more than 20 people;
 2. Be responsible for the assembly and production of automated jigs and equipment to meet customer delivery in a timely manner;
 3. Coordinate other R&D departments to solve problems in production, ensure quality and deliver to customers in a timely manner;
 4. Formulate detailed assembly production plans, coordinate human resources, divide work and cooperate, determine the time points required by customers, and complete assembly production in a timely manner;
 5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the assembly manufacturing team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for an Electrical Control Engineering Leader to join their team.

Main responsibilities:
 1. Be responsible for the formation of an electrical control PLC development team of more than 10 people;
 2. Be responsible for the overall planning and implementation of electrical control PLC development projects, formulate detailed project plans and timetables, and clarify the goals and deliverables of each stage;
 3. Monitor project progress, timely discover and solve problems in the project to ensure the project is completed on time and in accordance with quality requirements;
 4. Coordinate communication and collaboration within the project team and with other departments (such as mechanical design, electrical design, production, etc.) to ensure the smooth progress of the project (e.g., jointly solve equipment linkage problems with mechanical and electrical teams during the equipment installation and commissioning stage);
 5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the development team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

Working location: Bac Ninh (with shuttle bus from Hanoi)
We are supporting our client, a large company with an attractive benefits package, look for a Vision Application Development Leader to join their team.
Main responsibilities:
1. Be responsible for the formation of a vision development team of about 10 people;
2. Task allocation and technical guidance, formulate development specification and code review mechanisms;
3. Control the whole project cycle (demand analysis → POC verification → on-site commissioning → delivery acceptance) to ensure customer SLA compliance;
4. Coordinate cross-departmental resources (mechanical/electrical/software teams) to solve system integration conflicts;
5. Be responsible for the recruitment, training and performance appraisal of the development team to improve the overall technical level and work efficiency of the team.

